# Titanic Survival Prediction

## Overview
Predicted survival of Titanic passengers using passenger details like age, gender, and ticket class.

## Dataset
- Source: Kaggle - Titanic Machine Learning from Disaster
- Training: 891 rows, 12 columns
- Target: Survived (0 = No, 1 = Yes)

## Steps Followed
1. Loaded and explored dataset
2. Handled missing values - Age (median), Embarked (mode), dropped Cabin
3. Converted categorical columns to numbers
4. Trained Logistic Regression - 82% accuracy
5. Improved with Random Forest - 84% accuracy
6. Created submission file for Kaggle

## Results
- Logistic Regression: 82%
- Random Forest (max_depth=7): 84%

## Libraries Used
- Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn

## What I Learned
- Handling missing values strategically
- Feature engineering on real world data
- Random Forest outperforms Logistic Regression on structured data
- max_depth controls overfitting in Random Forest
